The development of language skills is important as it includes listening, speaking, reading and writing. Developing each skill means that the teacher is familiar with approriate methods, incl. game, and creates supportive learning environment.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give future preschool teachers an overview of the development of language skills (years 0-7) and prepare them for developing these skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course students  * will know the factors of the development of language skills at preschool age; * will be able to develop children's listening skills; * will know the factors influencing reading and writing skills; *can use different methods to teach reading considering children's skills and (special) needs; * can use games as part of learning; *can monitor children's language development and evaluate the efficiency of one's own work.
